/1377330687522111488?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'publisher': 'Recruit.net', 'apply_link': 'https://www.recruit.net/job/software-engineer-salesforce--jobs/B1C214905FD5A828?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'apply_link': 'https://www.roberthalf.com/sg/en/job/singapore/software-engineer-salesforce/67020-0013362657-sgen', 'is_direct': None, 'publisher': 'Robert Half'}], 'job_description': \"The CompanyOur client is a leading investment management firm with a strong regional presence. The organization places high importance on technology as a business enabler and continues to invest in its Salesforce platform to support sales, client coverage, and operational efficiency. This is a permanent, in-house position responsible for the application support, administration, and ongoing development of Salesforce Sales Cloud. The role plays a critical part in ensuring Salesforce remains stable, scalable, and aligned with the firm's asset management business requirements.The Role Provide end-to-end support, administration, and development of Salesforce Sales CloudDesign, build, and maintain Salesforce functionalities to support business processesPartner with business users to gather requirements and deliver sustainable technical solutionsManage and support integrations between Salesforce and enterprise systemsTroubleshoot production issues and drive root-cause analysis and permanent fixesContribute to platform enhancements, automation, and data optimization initiativesEnsure Salesforce solutions align with internal governance and best practiceSupport long-term platform roadmap and continuous improvement initiatives Your Profile At least 5 years of hands-on Salesforce development experience, with strong focus on Sales CloudExperience working in an asset management or investment management environmentProven experience supporting Salesforce in a permanent, enterprise settingSalesforce Platform Developer Certification (required)Strong analytical, problem-solving, and stakeholder management skillsSalesforce Sales CloudSnowflakeWorkato (iPaaS / integrations)Development C#, Front-end JavaScript jQuery Apply TodayPlease send your resume, in WORD format only and quote reference number DC13362657, by clicking the apply button. Please note that only short-listed candidates will be contacted.Robert Half International Pte Ltd. Co. Registration no.: 200612189E | EA Licence no.: 07C5595 | Dmitriy Chervinskyi EA Registration no.: R22108655By clicking 'apply', you give your express consent that Robert Half may use your personal information to process your job application and to contact you from time to time for future employment opportunities. For further information on how Robert Half processes your personal information and how to access and correct your information, please read the Robert Half privacy notice: https://www.roberthalf.com.sg/privacy-statement. Please do not submit any sensitive personal data to us in your resume (such as government ID numbers, ethnicity, gender, religion, marital status or trade union membership) as we do not collect your sensitive personal data at this time.\", 'job_is_remote': False, 'job_posted_at': None, 'job_posted_at_timestamp': None, 'job_posted_at_datetime_utc': None, 'job_location': 'Singapore', 'job_city': None, 'job_state': None, 'job_country': 'SG', 'job_latitude': 1.352083, 'job_longitude': 103.819836, 'job_benefits': None, 'job_google_link': 'https://www.google.com/search?q=jobs&gl=us&hl=en&udm=8#vhid=vt%3D20/docid%3D7dv5KFL-IKxzLkSgAAAAAA%3D%3D&vssid=jobs-detail-viewer', 'job_min_salary': None, 'job_max_salary': None, 'job_salary_period': 'MONTH', 'job_highlights': {}, 'job_onet_soc': '15113200', 'job_onet_job_zone': '4'}, {'job_id': 'yhz8ESsGl_xBMPIcAAAAAA==', 'job_title': 'Firmware Engineering Lead', 'employer_name': 'Advanced Micro Devices, Inc', 'employer_logo': None, 'employer_website': None, 'job_publisher': 'AMD Careers', 'job_employment_type': 'Full-time', 'job_employment_types': ['FULLTIME'], 'job_apply_link': 'https://careers.amd.com/careers-home/jobs/76672?lang=en-us&utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'job_apply_is_direct': True, 'apply_options': [{'publisher': 'AMD Careers', 'apply_link': 'https://careers.amd.com/careers-home/jobs/76672?lang=en-us&utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': True}, {'publisher': 'Jobstreet', 'apply_link': 'https://sg.jobstreet.com/job/89318859?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'publisher': 'Singapore Jobs Expertini', 'apply_link': 'https://sg.expertini.com/job/firmware-engineering-lead-singapore-advanced-micro-devices-inc-7ade91ae4bbc/?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'publisher': 'EchoJobs', 'apply_link': 'https://echojobs.io/job/amd-firmware-engineer-s8x3u?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': True}, {'publisher': 'ClickaJobs', 'apply_link': 'https://sg.clickajobs.com/jobs/firmware-engineering-lead?id=31973553&utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'apply_link': 'https://careers.amd.com/careers-home/jobs/76672?lang=en-us', 'is_direct': None, 'publisher': 'AMD Careers'}], 'job_description': 'WHAT YOU DO AT AMD CHANGES EVERYTHING\\n\\nAt AMD, our mission is to build great products that accelerate next-generation computing experiences—from AI and data centers, to PCs, gaming and embedded systems. Grounded in a culture of innovation and collaboration, we believe real progress comes from bold ideas, human ingenuity and a shared passion to create something extraordinary. When you join AMD, you’ll discover the real differentiator is our culture. We push the limits of innovation to solve the world’s most important challenges—striving for execution excellence, while being direct, humble, collaborative, and inclusive of diverse perspectives. Join us as we shape the future of AI and beyond. Together, we advance your career.\\n\\nTHE ROLE:\\n\\nWe are looking for an SMTS (Senior Member of Technical Staff) Engineer with an obsession for firmware. As part of the role, the SMTS Engineer will work closely with other firmware engineers, developers and architects across various IPs in leading the designs and implementing firmware that spans pre-silicon and post-silicon for all AMD SoCs.\\u202f\\n\\nTHE PERSON:\\n\\nYou are passionate about firmware development with creative and effective problem-solving skills, a motivated, self-starter who can work both independently and collaboratively in fast paced environments. You have excellent technical communication, interpersonal and leadership skills.\\n\\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES:\\n• Lead Engineer responsible for designing, developing, debugging, verifying and/or validating firmware, software and/or hardware\\n• Lead day-to-day firmware development work\\n• Provide consultation to internal and external customers regarding AMD features and programming requirements\\n\\nPREFERRED EXPERIENCE:\\n• Multiple prior years of related firmware experience combined with technical education within the semiconductor industry\\n• Expert level experience producing quality firmware\\n\\nACADEMIC CREDENTIALS:\\n• Bachelor’s or Master’s degree (preferred) in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or equivalent\\n\\nLOCATION:\\n\\nSingapore\\n\\n#LI-CK1\\n\\nBenefits offered are described: AMD benefits at a glance.\\n\\nAMD does not accept unsolicited resumes from headhunters, recruitment agencies, or fee-based recruitment services. AMD and its subsidiaries are equal opportunity, inclusive employers and will consider all applicants without regard to age, ancestry, color, marital status, medical condition, mental or physical disability, national origin, race, religion, political and/or third-party affiliation, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. We encourage applications from all qualified candidates and will accommodate applicants’ needs under the respective laws throughout all stages of the recruitment and selection process.\\n\\nAMD may use Artificial Intelligence to help screen, assess or select applicants for this position. AMD’s “Responsible AI Policy” is available here.\\n\\nThis posting is for an existing vacancy.', 'job_is_remote': False, 'job_posted_at': None, 'job_posted_at_timestamp': None, 'job_posted_at_datetime_utc': None, 'job_location': 'Singapore', 'job_city': None, 'job_state': None, 'job_country': 'SG', 'job_latitude': 1.352083, 'job_longitude': 103.819836, 'job_benefits': None, 'job_google_link': 'https://www.google.com/search?q=jobs&gl=us&hl=en&udm=8#vhid=vt%3D20/docid%3Dyhz8ESsGl_xBMPIcAAAAAA%3D%3D&vssid=jobs-detail-viewer', 'job_salary': None, 'job_min_salary': None, 'job_max_salary': None, 'job_salary_period': None, 'job_highlights': {}, 'job_onet_soc': '15113300', 'job_onet_job_zone': '4'}, {'job_id': '0XpPcxNn12sGdgJGAAAAAA==', 'job_title': 'Software Engineer, Behaviors Research', 'employer_name': 'MOTIONAL SINGAPORE PTE. LIMITED', 'employer_logo': 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS1FhfMzXixa21Yth6ppJOuzCrZ0tBFpJ0LqkN9&s=0', 'employer_website': None, 'job_publisher': 'MyCareersFuture', 'job_employment_type': 'Full-time', 'job_employment_types': ['FULLTIME'], 'job_apply_link': 'https://www.mycareersfuture.gov.sg/job/information-technology/software-engineer-behaviors-research-motional-singapore-5dd63ea16eb3a34386749c4912b8c254?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'job_apply_is_direct': False, 'apply_options': [{'publisher': 'MyCareersFuture', 'apply_link': 'https://www.mycareersfuture.gov.sg/job/information-technology/software-engineer-behaviors-research-motional-singapore-5dd63ea16eb3a34386749c4912b8c254?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'publisher': 'Jooble', 'apply_link': 'https://sg.jooble.org/jdp/-3887395488864619935?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'publisher': 'Jobrapido.com', 'apply_link': 'https://sg.jobrapido.com/jobpreview/237963979442356224?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'is_direct': False}, {'apply_link': 'https://www.mycareersfuture.gov.sg/job/information-technology/software-engineer-behaviors-research-motional-singapore-5dd63ea16eb3a34386749c4912b8c254', 'is_direct': None, 'publisher': 'MyCareersFuture'}], 'job_description': 'What you’ll be doing:\\n• Conduct research on driving behavior related topics, such as future prediction, motion planning, agent simulation, scenario generation\\n• Work with large-scale internal datasets to demonstrate the effectiveness of your research\\n• Collaborate with different teams to deploy your research results into the autonomous vehicles\\n• Publish the research results in papers and patents\\n\\nWhat we are looking for:\\n• Enrolled in a Masters or PhD program in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Robotics or similar technical field of study\\n• Strong Machine Learning research background with publications in any of the top-tier conferences(RSS, ICRA, CoRL, CVPR, ICRL, ICML, NeurIPS, etc.)\\n• Proficiency in Python coding and PyTorch or other commonly-used deep learning frameworks\\n• One-team mindset and effective collaboration with other researchers and engineers\\n• Strong communication and interpersonal skills\\n• Previous experience in autonomous driving is preferred', 'job_is_remote': False, 'job_posted_at': '27 days ago', 'job_posted_at_timestamp': 1770163200, 'job